Commentary Text: Lamichhane to Sam Curran, out Caught&Bowled!! Second wicket in the over. What a day Lamichhane is having. Belted by KL, picked his wicket. Smashed around the park by Gayle, sent him back as well and now picks another. The googly which sticks in the surface a tad more than Curran expected, he is early into the back foot push and lobs a dolly back to Lamichhane. He flings it up and pumps his fist. Boy isn't he delighted. Sam Curran c and b Lamichhane 0(4)

Commentary Text: Lamichhane to Gayle, out Caught by Axar!! Stunning work! This is the perfect definition of team work by Ingram and Axar. Lamichhane has traveled a lot but will be relieved to see the back of Gayle. The wrong 'un which is fraction short, Gayle does not get enough power behind the pull shot, skies it to deep mid-wicket where Ingram is waiting, he takes it right on the edge of the boundary cushion and since the momentum was taking him over, he threw the ball all the way to Axar near long-on. The back hand flick was just perfect as Axar didn't have to move much. Huge moment in the game. Gayle c Axar b Lamichhane 69(37) [4s-6 6s-5]

Commentary Text: Lamichhane to Rahul, out Stumped!! Appeal for a stumping and Pant looks confident. He's on the line and that means KL is OUT. That's some comeback from Lamichhane, a beaut of a leg-break, drifted in from outside off, dragged Rahul forward and then spun past his outside edge. Rahul was lunging forward in defence, dragged his right-foot out and Pant is quick enough to whip the bails - even as Rahul's feet stayed static on the line. Good bargain for Lamichhane, 10 runs and a big wicket so far. Rahul st Pant b Lamichhane 12(9) [4s-1 6s-1]
